&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Get ready for&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Gear up for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is an idiom that means&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;prepare or equip oneself for something; get ready.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; -&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Now the country needs to &lt;strong&gt;gear up for &lt;/strong&gt;backing&amp;nbsp;the domestic economy.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;So,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;get ready for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the&amp;nbsp;most appropriate meaning of the given idiom.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 4)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;i.e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;moderate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-200a6302-7fff-c1cf-2632-b5faa3c35d0b&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border: none; display: inline-block; overflow: hidden; width: 40px; height: 35px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;35&quot; src=&quot;https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/28i2H4qZUMqoricKhH6aaLqxFoqVxqpmaJpMBy62DoGJbWBmmYJxPuBF6Wq_gGqfYCkpEpr0WIm9NnvtUCdNGqm-1_wqVyF46346wBwUiFK7AiZX8LxkL7abs3B0GOqVQ9Wwde-d&quot; style=&quot;margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 0px;&quot; width=&quot;40&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Explanation&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Exorbitant&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; means exceeding the customary or appropriate limits in intensity, quality, amount, or size.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;synonyms&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the word are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;excessive, extravagant, extreme, fancy, immoderate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;antonyms&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the word are&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;moderate, modest, reasonable, temperate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;From&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;antonym&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Exorbitant&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;, we can say that the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;moderate&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is its&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;opposite meaning&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;moderate&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;observing reasonable limits.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hence&lt;/span&gt;, we can say that &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;moderate&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is nearly opposite in meaning to the given word.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Let&amp;#39;s see the meaning of other given options-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

	&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;tbody style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
			&lt;tr style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;WORDS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;MEANING&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
